1.m_mItemDesc:
"Ancient memories echo through rifts in time and space, awaiting the arrival of the destined one. Use these fragments to increase your Lord Level.
<alpha=#80>The Church dreads Black Blood due its vast reservoir of memories. Upon mere contact, most will be instantly vanquished by this ocean of memories; only a select few have the ability to draw strength from it."

2.m_mItemDesc:
"Can be used to purchase items in the Boutique.
<alpha=#80>They say when the glimmers dance across the night sky, a new star is soon to rise."

99.m_mItemDesc:
"Crystals created by primordial alchemists using Red Lunarite. Moon Tear (Free) is consumed first. When insufficient, Moon Tear (Paid) will be consumed automatically.
<alpha=#80>The ancients once placed their longing for ultimate life in the full moon. The crystals refined from Red Lunarite naturally form into teardrop shapes, hence alchemists named them Moon Tear."

100.m_mItemDesc:
"Crystals created by ancient alchemists using Red Lunarite. Prioritizes Moon Tear (Free), and when insufficient, Moon Tear (Paid) will be consumed.
<alpha=#80>The ancients once associated immortality with the crescent moon. As the crystals refined from Lunarite naturally form into a teardrop-shape, alchemists have named them 'Moon Tear.'"

101.m_mItemDesc:
"Crystals created by ancient alchemists using Red Lunarite. Prioritizes Moon Tear (Free), and when insufficient, Moon Tear (Paid) will be consumed.
<alpha=#80>The ancients once associated immortality with the crescent moon. As the crystals refined from Lunarite naturally form into a teardrop-shape, alchemists have named them 'Moon Tear.'"

998.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to upgrade Hall of Honor and, when enough are collected, gain permanent bonuses.
<alpha=#80>The badge, polished to perfection, has clearly been well cared for, though its previous owner remains unknown. Regardless, past honor always paves a path for the future."

999.m_mItemDesc:
"The currency used for all transactions across Minexus. Made from precious metal, it is stamped with a seal representing the Church's "gift of justice and order."
<alpha=#80>Introduced as the standard currency following the Tempus Church's unification of the continent, these coins were minted from tamper-proof "Liquid Gold" by the legendary alchemist Albrecht, Sage of Holy Water. His technique represented a crystallization of wisdom far beyond the limitations of his era."

1001.m_mItemDesc:
"Crimson-colored Ether used for increasing Vassal Level.
<alpha=#80>Floating on the surface are strange symbols, barely visible. They appear to be recording some kind of complicated information."

1002.m_mItemDesc:
"A rare substance that shouldn't exist in this world, yet can make everything here grow rapidly. Used to increase Vassal Level
<alpha=#80>Periodically descends from another realm, constantly shifting between liquid and crystal states. The memories concealed within represent the shared experiences of all matter. "The blood of the divine shall fall unto the earth like shooting stars.""

1003.m_mItemDesc:
"A circular ribbon that can be given to friends. Used to Embrace during Celestial Concerto.
<alpha=#80>Nobles once exchanged these ribbons as symbols of acquaintance. However, because they contain "memories," they have since been banned by the Tempus Church. Very few still maintain this ritual today."

1049.m_mItemDesc:
"A scroll inscribed with formulas of Bloodborn Alchemy. Used for Crescent Moon Embrace.
<alpha=#80>A parchment glowing faintly, etched with the most fundamental Bloodborn Alchemy formulas. It serves as a Covenant for all new Bloodborn, an echo of ancient memories, a call to the purest form of life."

1050.m_mItemDesc:
"A scroll inscribed with formulas of Bloodborn Alchemy. Used to recruit Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Legend whispers that alchemists believed blood to be a vessel of collective memories. While life is fleeting, memory paves the way to immortality. In their pursuit, they crafted a formula capable of resurrecting the memories of the deceased and passing them on."

1051.m_mItemDesc:
"A scroll inscribed with formulas of Bloodborn Alchemy. Used to recruit featured Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Long forgotten and buried in dust due to obscurity. Until one day, a young alchemist uncovered its potential to unlock memories from the depths of time."

1052.m_mItemDesc:
"A mysterious red powder left behind after performing an Embrace ritual. Collect a certain amount to exchange for featured Vassals.
<alpha=#80>While researching memory fusion, ancient alchemists discovered that the body couldn't withstand memory surges, so they began grinding rings into powder to mitigate any adverse effects on the physical form."

1053.m_mItemDesc:
"A black powdery residue left behind after performing certain Embrace rituals. Collect a certain amount to exchange for featured Vassals.
<alpha=#80> The Ring of Shadows, having been forsaken and weathered by time's cruel touch, remains as fragments of obsidian. Despite still harboring the memory of ancient deities, these fractured remnants have long since relinquished their powers of transmission."

1054.m_mItemDesc:
"Title documents issued by the Church, used to change a Lord's name.
<alpha=#80> Documents are emblem of sovereign right, bestowed upon Lords by the Tempus Church, elevating them to a position of power to manage in the Church's name."

1055.m_mItemDesc:
"Converted from repeatedly obtained Vassals once Spirit Siphon is maxed out. The vessel contains familiar blood and memories. Used to exchange for items in the Covenant Shop.
<alpha=#80>As blood begins to disperse, the memories will fade. Thus, the alchemists extract the human soul which connects the two, in order to temporarily preserve memories."

1056.m_mItemDesc:
"Gauntlet entry ticket. Allows entry into the Blood Arena - Gauntlet.
<alpha=#80>Once a form of friendly competition, it has since turned into a fierce proving grounds of one's might and mettle."

1057.m_mItemDesc:
"A license to kill. Allows entry into the Blood Arena - Crucible.
<alpha=#80>After countless attempts to outlaw it, the Church now referees this gruesome crucible, originally established by the major families to weed out the weak."

1058.m_mItemDesc:
"Stone tablet bearing the name of a duelist. Used for the Crucible's point ranking.
<alpha=#80>In the first Holy War, the Tempus Church carved the names of the fallen on stone. Now, Arena referees inscribe the names of victors upon a keystone, perhaps following the ancients."

1059.m_mItemDesc:
"A testament to bravery. Used to make purchases in the Blood Shop.
<alpha=#80>Legend has it that after each duel, slaves would harvest fighters' blood from the battlefield and drain it into the stone tablet to serve as genuine proof of their courage."

1060.m_mItemDesc:
"A pledge of unwavering loyalty between clan members, can be purchased from the Clan Shop.
<alpha=#80>Oaths engraved on silver coins bear the ancestral covenant: "Thou shall not follow me, for I may not lead; Thou shall not walk ahead of me, for I may not follow; Nay, let us march as comrades, united.""

1061.m_mItemDesc:
"Precious cellar-aged wine, safeguarded by the family for generations. Pour it into an Ancient Coffer to awaken a powerful Vassal from an era bygone.
<alpha=#80>Light of life, flame of desire."

1070.m_mItemDesc:
"Etched with mysterious symbols that, after repeated forging, emit a curious red glow. Used for Soul Echo, Equipment Recast, and Refining.
<alpha=#80>Before forging techniques were discovered, ancient craftsmen used these to temper metal. Today, alchemists engrave them with symbols, in attempt to craft unseen wonders."

1071.m_mItemDesc:
"A worn parchment depicts the artifacts once worn by heroes. Clear [Tomb of the Fallen] to obtain random Equipment.
<alpha=#80>Like a shell to its pearl, these artifacts bind and protect their bearer."

1075.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to activate the Talent Tree in the Timeworn Mausoleum. An oddly-shaped compass that only seems to work in certain areas.
<alpha=#80>The needle guides the way, bringing salvation to those who are lost."

1101.m_mItemDesc:
"Gray ore used to upgrade and enhance equipment. Provides 100 Equipment EXP.
<alpha=#80>This common ore strewn about the realm was once viewed as a divine blessing, and only Church-sanctioned guilds were allowed to excavate."

1102.m_mItemDesc:
"Hardened ore coated in a black shell, used to upgrade and enhance equipment. Provides 1,000 Equipment EXP.
<alpha=#80>Alchemists believe that blackened ore enhances the smelting process. Most of the supply is controlled by the Church, though some still circulates on the market."

1201.m_mItemDesc:
"Meteorite stone radiating sparks. Basic material used for upgrading Ultimates.
<alpha=#80>Alchemists used to inscribe memories into these stones in the hopes of finding a new means to perpetuate their existence."

1202.m_mItemDesc:
"Meteorite stone enveloped in flames. Quality material used for upgrading Ultimates.
<alpha=#80>Flames envelop these stones, alit by some special material. This was the technique alchemists used to ward off memory theft."

1203.m_mItemDesc:
"Meteorite stone engulfed in powerful flames, whose heat stands as a true trial for believers. High-quality material used for upgrading Ultimates.
<alpha=#80>Memories and will are safeguarded inside by searing flames— a proud work of the ancient alchemists. Should one wish to inherit them, one must endure the fiery crucible."

1204.m_mItemDesc:
"Filled with the cherished sagas of bards. Use to upgrade Specials.
<alpha=#80>According to legends, Seth, The Tempus Church's Holy Mother and agent of Aeon, recorded lore and history on ancient parchment to enlighten the masses."

1205.m_mItemDesc:
"Its pages are filled with the chronicles of the Church. Used to upgrade Specials.
<alpha=#80>Sages have trodden the solemn path, and devout followers shall seek to heed their counsel, be it ignorantly or willfully, painfully or happily."

1206.m_mItemDesc:
"Its pages are filled with prophecies of ancient gods. Used to upgrade Specials.
<alpha=#80>Tempus Church Scholars diligently inscribed divine prophecies onto parchment, their pages now scattered across the land for reasons unbeknownst to any."

1207.m_mItemDesc:
"Used for skill reset. A mysterious chronometer etched with intricate runes and winding patterns.
<alpha=#80>An heirloom of the Alita family. They say a mere swipe can rewind time itself."

1301.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Warrior. High-quality material used for upgrading Warrior Skills.
<alpha=#80>Having emerged triumphantly from eight decisive holy wars, the Church no longer had to worry about its collapse. Upon his retirement, the Church clandestinely sealed this warrior's legacy, shrouding him in secrecy for eternity."

1302.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Assassin. High-quality material used for upgrading Assassin Skills.
<alpha=#80>Once the hidden blade of the Astolfo family, she became exiled by way of an internal power struggle. Forty years later, she returned under a moonless sky, channeling her humiliation into a bloodbath, exacting retribution upon all those who had betrayed her."

1303.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Defender. High-quality material used for upgrading Defender Skills.
<alpha=#80>That was the last time she set up a tent to shelter her people from the ravages of time. There were no secrets kept from the Tempus Church, alas the tent was eventually confiscated by Bell Ringers, and so it was that her silent guardianship became doomed to obscurity."

1304.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Marksman. High-quality material used for upgrading Marksman Skills.
<alpha=#80>He soaked his bow in a vat of Black Blood for half a century, and the arrows became imbued with the eternal memory of the Black Blood Beast, relentlessly chasing their target until the ends of the earth."

1305.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Sorcerer. High-quality material used for upgrading Sorcerer Skills.
<alpha=#80>She communed with the heavens, which presented her shooting stars that foretold of a cataclysm. Before she could make it to town, she passed in the mountains, leaving behind only a few pieces of her secrets."

1306.m_mItemDesc:
"Sealed with the secrets of a legendary Enchanter. High-quality material used for upgrading Enchanter Skills.
<alpha=#80>As the right hand of the Saint, she wove the Threads of Fate, with each strand portending a destiny. Yet in defiance of Church decrees, she clandestinely altered the needlework, thereby sparing the heretics from their assured doom."

<alpha=#80>Will the pain ever fade?"

<alpha=#80>Whenever some poor soul returns from a voyage, there's always a story to tell."

1413.m_mItemDesc:
"A yellowed letter containing names blurred beyond recognition.
<alpha=#80>In times of chaos, even words became a luxury."

<alpha=#80>They bestow new insight into this broken world."

1416.m_mItemDesc:

1420.m_mItemDesc:
"A curiously-shaped key of mysterious origins, able to unlock the Ancestral Vault in Dusk Castle.
<alpha=#80>Rumor has it that sealed deep within the castle walls are the heroic warriors from that era, awaiting descendants of the Bathory family to come to awaken them and once again reclaim their past glory."

1421.m_mItemDesc:
"A lavish key adorned with intricate patterns, able to unlock the Hall of Opulence in Dusk Castle. 
<alpha=#80>This hallway houses the dust-covered history of the Bathory family, long into its decline. But now, hope has once again returned."

1422.m_mItemDesc:
"A wooden key whose bow resembles an eye gazing upon the world. Used to unlock the Eye of God in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>The birch forest whispers echoes of lament, its skeletons buried in the mist, marking the scars of Ganelon. A cartographer once built a cabin atop the hill to survey nature's wonders. But alas, as war spread, the key was lost to time, somewhere in Minexus."

1423.m_mItemDesc:
"A pitch-black key, devoid of light, as if summoned from the depths of hell. Used to unlock the Crescent Garden in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>The garden had enchanted the lives of the Bathorys once upon a time, but as the long night descended and faith faltered, all that remained were wild roses under the light of the moon."

1424.m_mItemDesc:
"A bat-shaped key forged from teeth, crafted for extraordinary purposes. Used to unlock Wailing Crypts in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>Forged from the fangs of Bathory tomb guardians, the snow-white bone reflects their fierce nature. Their sharp edges resemble the piercing howls of the forsaken, echoing in the depths of this long night."

1425.m_mItemDesc:
"An incredibly simple key, its head worn and rusted by the passage of time. Used to unlock the Mouret Mill in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>This humble key once held the modest wishes of Mouret's villagers: Three meals a day and long, healthy life. After the Black Blood appeared, even simple wishes became unattainable."

1426.m_mItemDesc:
"This key's bow is adorned with a gleaming gemstone encased in copper, emitting a soft glow even in the darkest of nights. Used to unlock the Fangtooth Tower in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>Sentinels used to guard the tower, but following the Bloodborn's fall from grace, all that remained was crumbled stone. Of all the finely crafted keys, only this one still stands proud, as if defying time itself."

1427.m_mItemDesc:
"An iron key adorned with shards resembling fragments of volcanic rock. Used to unlock the Ethereal Springs in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>After surviving a volcanic eruption, a young girl picked up a piece of fallen debris at her feet and swore an oath upon it to protect her family's surviving members."

1428.m_mItemDesc:
"A silver key adorned with intricate snow patterns, flawless and pure. Used to unlock the Thawpoint Lodge in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>He was once a boy who raced across snow-white plains. What was it that compelled his soul to linger in this desolate, snowy night?"

1429.m_mItemDesc:
"A wooden key, roughly carved into the shape of a fish bone. Used to unlock the Cerulean Fishing Village in Starlit Memoir.
<alpha=#80>As a child, he carved this wooden fish bone as a gift, using nothing but stone. Twenty years later, his hands— now worn and weathered— hold the hand of the one who kept that gift, and together they enter the room that accepts it as a key."

1430.m_mItemDesc:
"A gift prepared by Bella. Can be used to collect gifts in the Bella's Privy Patrons event.
<alpha=#80>Each Puppet is chosen with care, a quiet testament to Bella's trust in you. Rest assured, these Puppets rest soundly beneath the veil of night."

Aiona has lifted it countless times, only to let it slip back into the sands.
Can be used to perform Herald x10 in Cycle of Destruction."

<alpha=#80>One of the materials used to inherit memory, Very scarce in quantity, only select organizations like the Tempus Church have access to it. During the Age of Enlightenment, many believed engraving words on stone was the only way to preserve memory and knowledge."

30011.m_mItemDesc:
"A bundle of scrolls detailing the origins of different bloodlines. Used to gain Knowledge.
<alpha=#80>Curated by nobles, these texts, though quite aged and faded, exude extraordinary sagacity."

30012.m_mItemDesc: "Detailed records of celestial and earthly wisdom. Use to gain basic materials needed for upgrading certain Ultimates and Specials.<alpha=#80>Believers hold that their firm faith in a higher form of existence bears promise of eternal life. Non-believers contend that the heart is naive, and man would be wise not to offer everything to the gods. The rarely enlightened understand that there is in fact no conflict between the two."

30013.m_mItemDesc:

<alpha=#80>Countless corpses litter the entrance of the gloomy cave; many have never even touched it."

30014.m_mItemDesc:

<alpha=#80>Though the moon waxes and wanes, we remain under its vigil."

30015.m_mItemDesc:

<alpha=#80>A world capable of soaking in the moon's radiance must also endure countless sunsets."

110002.m_mItemDesc: "Activates Full Moon Pact for 30 days upon use."

110003.m_mItemDesc: "Activates Premium rewards for the current Boon From Afar upon use."

500001.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enter the Twilight Path. A thick, shriveled umbilical cord so short it's hard to tell what kind of creature it belongs to.
<alpha=#80>The life it once nurtured has long since vanished, yet its surface still emits an uncanny glow. Its hardened tip has been molded into an irregular shape, serving as a key to the far side of the moon."

500002.m_mItemDesc:
"A delicate silver flower that blooms under the ethereal glow of moonlight. Use to exchange for items in Far Side of the Moon Event Shop - Moondream Journey.
<alpha=#80>This silver blossom, averse to the heat of the sun, blooms only under the light of the moon. At one time, Moonblossoms became associated with the Bloodborn, upon which they were decreed heretical and exterminated by the Church."

500003.m_mItemDesc:
"A napkin stained with blood. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>Initially meant to hide debris, it now covers the empty hole in her chest. There is still some warmth left in it, almost as if one could sense her insatiable hunger."

500004.m_mItemDesc:
"A round lead mirror spotted with rust. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>The once sparkling mirror has since lost its shine, its frame coated in rust. The girl used to see countless reflections in the mirror, with each face being similar to her own."

500005.m_mItemDesc:
"The shattered remains of a lute. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>Though its strings had long since snapped off, faint lines on the neck revealed their former location. The instrument itself still gave off a faint melody, seemingly the notes once played by the girl."

500006.m_mItemDesc:
"The remains of something burned to ashes. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>The ashes of an unknown object, still radiating with the heat of flame. Buried under the coals is the heart of the girl, still pumping with rage."

500007.m_mItemDesc:
"White petals that have dried up. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>Though the petals withered following her departure, her tenderness lingers in the pistils, serving as evidence of her nurturing touch."

500008.m_mItemDesc:
"A weathered book page laden with indecipherable text and faded illustrations. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>Lacking a cover, the crumbling pages give off the damp aroma of the Bathory Castle halls. The girl yearned to comprehend her existence in its passages, but the twisted words demonstrate her failure."

500009.m_mItemDesc:
"Decaying brown chips of wood, once part of a coffin. Collect to enter Memory Shards.
<alpha=#80>The girl sunk herself in it, attempting to isolate herself from the filth and chaos of the world. Though only a portion of the coffin remains, one can still sense her contempt for the world outside in its rotting fumes."

500011.m_mItemDesc:
"Flipping the Tarot cards unlocks the event stage "Accursed Journey."
<alpha=#80>The deity who created such esoteric rituals has long abandoned humanity. Where will the humble and foolish daily prayers drift to above the clouds?"

500012.m_mItemDesc:
"Use Crude Coins to redeem event items at the Vagabond's Encampment.
<alpha=#80>Should you place your ear next to the shell, the distant sound of waves and fish leaping from the water can be heard. Perhaps they were once used by a sea-faring people?"

500031.m_mItemDesc:
"Can be used to enter event stages.
<alpha=#80>Sunscreen crafted by Lorelei using Tidewisp powder. When applying it, even the Bloodborn to briefly venture into sunlight."

500032.m_mItemDesc:
"Can be redeemed for items at the event shop Sapphire Isle Auction House.
<alpha=#80>A copper coin engraved with the Sage Association emblem. It can be redeemed for exclusive items on the Isle, functioning like real currency."

500033.m_mItemDesc:
"Can be used to enter event stages.
<alpha=#80>Sunscreen crafted by Lorelei using Tidewisp powder. When applying it, even the Bloodborn to briefly venture into sunlight."

500051.m_mItemDesc:
"An hourglass that reverses time and unlocks the event stage in Ashes of Time.
<alpha=#80>If we could turn back the clock of time, would we find one last chance to do what we once dreamed of?"

500052.m_mItemDesc:
"A crown once cherished. Can be redeemed for items at the event shop Crumbling Bazaar.
<alpha=#80>One after another, they lie scattered in golden sand. Who owned this glory, and where will it truly belong?"

500053.m_mItemDesc:
"An hourglass that reverses time and unlocks the event stage in Ashes of Time.
<alpha=#80>If we could turn back the clock of time, would we find one last chance to do what we once dreamed of?"

500061.m_mItemDesc:
"Light the Lantern to unlock the story event "Against The Dying Light." A light essential for traversing the darkness.
<alpha=#80> In the depths of the dark night, who is it that still dreams of day?"

500062.m_mItemDesc:
"Light the Lantern to unlock the story event "Against The Dying Light." A light essential for traversing the darkness.
<alpha=#80> In the depths of the dark night, who is it that still dreams of day?"

500063.m_mItemDesc:
"Use fragments to redeem event items in "Timewalker's Satchel." A page from the Cartographer's atlas, recording her hasty observations.
<alpha=#80> Travelling 600 years back, I found that drawing concealed the coordinates which altered history."

800001.m_mItemDesc:
"A bland pot of green tea served to Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Remember, it's not the tea that matters, but the companionship."

800002.m_mItemDesc:
"A fragrant pot of Earl Grey tea served to Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>When the clock strikes four, everything stops for tea."

800003.m_mItemDesc:
"A pot of exotic fruit-infused tea paired with delicious snacks served to Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>First goes the tea, followed by the milk, then stir from twelve to six. When with friends, feel free to forego the formalities."

800011.m_mItemDesc:
"A small flask filled with starry liquid, served to Ancestral Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>There must be light, no matter how dim it is."

800012.m_mItemDesc:
"A fancy chalice filled with starry liquid, served to Ancestral Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Can this really be called "food"?"

800013.m_mItemDesc:
"An exquisite chalice filled with starry liquid, served to Ancestral Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Some seek out the flavors; others give up."

800021.m_mItemDesc:
"Classic meal for the Tempus Church served to Church Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Do all truths come out after wine?"

800022.m_mItemDesc:
"Classic meal for the Tempus Church served to Church Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Engrained in the souls of countless believers."

800023.m_mItemDesc:
"Classic meal for the Tempus Church served to Church Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>"One must examine oneself before partaking in these sacred morsels.""

800031.m_mItemDesc:
"Slightly roasted tender steak, served to Bloodborn Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Ask for no more than a simple meal during a rough journey."

800032.m_mItemDesc:
"Slightly roasted tender steak with aromatic blood essence. Served to Bloodborn Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Violent yet elegant."

800033.m_mItemDesc:
"Slightly roasted tender steak with aromatic blood essence. Served to Bloodborn Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Only Bloodborn Elders can afford such luxury."

800041.m_mItemDesc:
"Exquisitely cooked fresh seafood, served to Kingdom Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Good ingredients often only require the simplest cooking methods."

800042.m_mItemDesc:
"Exquisitely cooked fresh seafood with colorful vegetables, served to Kingdom Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Its complexity of flavor is always impressive."

800043.m_mItemDesc:
"Exquisitely cooked fresh seafood with colorful vegetables, served to Kingdom Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>A testament to the abundant resources and sophisticated food culture among the kingdoms on the Minexus continent."

800051.m_mItemDesc:
"Strange food from an unknown realm, served to Otherworldly Vassals. Simple meal, slightly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>"Is this what they eat?""

800052.m_mItemDesc:
"Strange food from an unknown realm, served to Otherworldly Vassals. Fancy meal, moderately heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Hard to imagine its taste."

800053.m_mItemDesc:
"Strange food from an unknown realm, served to Otherworldly Vassals. Luxury meal, greatly heightens Affinity.
<alpha=#80>Might be delicious, but requires courage to try."

900001.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Philosopher's Stone." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts an artifact fitted with strange metal parts, seemingly from another era. The Tempus Church created this at great costs to achieve the power of time travel."

900002.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Silvershadow Chronometer." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts a small metal dial with circular scales and two needles marking the cycle of day and night. Only Ancestral Nobles and esteemed Tempus Church members could possess such a gadget in ancient times."

900003.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Eye of Truth." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts a perplexing cylindrical structure. Employed by the Tempus Church to gaze into the void located at the end of the world."

900004.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Poseidon's Skull." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it seems to be some kind of circular device worn on the head. Though it is just a drawing, one can already sense its weight."

900005.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Fruit of Immortality." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts transparent liquid in a glass container that resists death. Used by the Tempus Church to heal soldiers during the Holy War against the Bloodborn, it earned the title of "Immortality.""

900006.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Nightingale's Invisible Cage." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts a wooden casing so intricate that likely no one could reproduce it. Rumor has it that someone once heard the song of a nightingale coming from inside."

900007.m_mItemDesc:
"Used to enhance the Future Artifact "Soul-binding Reliquary." Though under ownership of the Church, it has somehow fallen into civilian hands.
<alpha=#80>Delineated with intricate patterns and geometric lattices, it depicts a square frame with intricate parts that came from the East. Craftsmen have tried to build it, but had their souls stolen, falling into eternal sleep upon its creation."

901001.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of all Vassals.
<alpha=#80>These seemingly ephemeral and fleeting beings contain answers about the origin of the world."

901002.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Light Equipment Vassals.
<alpha=#80>It is said that the soul of an ordinary person weighs only as much as a single copper coin."

901003.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Medium Equipment Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Neither as fleeting as morning mist, nor as steadfast as a rock, it strikes the perfect balance."

901004.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Heavy Equipment Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Saturated with memories, it is a soul that cannot be salvaged."

901005.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Ancestral Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Drifting beyond life and death, these essences remain devoid of warmth or enclosures."

901006.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Church Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Sharp and methodical, they uphold order until the very end."

901007.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Bloodborn Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Thick, scorching, and entwined with countless memories."

901008.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Kingdom Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Tense and trembling, it seems to be struggling to break free from a curse."

901009.m_mItemDesc:
"Offer as sacrifices in the Ritual Chamber to enhance the attributes of Otherworldly Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Distant and faint, a glimmer of light points to a mysterious beyond."
